00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:16,640 --> 00:00:18,180
Sakuraba.

2
00:00:21,860 --> 00:00:28,060
This ceremony will help Sayaka and I move on.

3
00:00:28,060 --> 00:00:32,280
You didn't invite Kaori Wakamatsu.

4
00:00:34,210 --> 00:00:38,610
She may be Sayaka's mother.
But she's also the culprit.

5
00:00:39,220 --> 00:00:41,640
Hayashida.

6
00:00:42,340 --> 00:00:45,140
<i>I've made a massive oversight.</i>

7
00:00:46,350 --> 00:00:47,970
Mrs. Wakamatsu?

8
00:00:48,620 --> 00:00:50,340
One moment, please.

9
00:00:50,340 --> 00:00:52,470
I am the bride's mother.

10
00:00:52,470 --> 00:00:55,810
Allow me to inform Mr. Hayashida first.

11
00:00:57,290 --> 00:01:01,780
The culprit may be someone else entirely.

12
00:01:09,930 --> 00:01:11,090
[Gentlemen]

13
00:01:11,090 --> 00:01:15,230
Jesus, how many times will we repeat this?

14
00:01:15,230 --> 00:01:17,850
As many times as we need to.

15
00:01:17,850 --> 00:01:19,500
Kazuomi doesn't seem to mind.

16
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:23,200
They could at least refund us
for our first wedding gifts.

17
00:01:23,200 --> 00:01:25,020
He's practically ripping us off.

18
00:01:25,020 --> 00:01:27,630
Sayaka has such bad taste.
[Ladies]

19
00:01:27,630 --> 00:01:30,470
It's like our warning meant nothing to her.

20
00:01:30,470 --> 00:01:31,870
Do you think they'll last a year?

21
00:01:31,870 --> 00:01:33,550
Absolutely not.

22
00:01:33,550 --> 00:01:35,610
Especially with that husband of hers.

23
00:01:52,060 --> 00:01:54,840
<i>You ought to consider canceling.</i>

24
00:01:59,880 --> 00:02:03,420
No. We won't be canceling.

25
00:02:03,420 --> 00:02:05,970
Sayaka and I prepared ourselves for this day.

26
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:09,080
This is for Sayaka's sake.

27
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:14,560
Folks, please ready your glasses.

28
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:22,020
Your glasses, please.

29
00:02:25,550 --> 00:02:29,970
To the bride and groom's blessed future.

30
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:35,060
Cheers.

31
00:02:35,060 --> 00:02:37,000
Cheers.

32
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:12,820
Folks, I thank you all for attending today.

33
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,580
How delicious.

34
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:34,820
We will now present a special slideshow

35
00:03:34,820 --> 00:03:38,120
of the happy memories shared

36
00:03:38,120 --> 00:03:40,740
between the illustrious bride and groom.

37
00:03:40,740 --> 00:03:44,000
Please, sit back and enjoy.

38
00:03:47,950 --> 00:03:51,180
[September 14th, 1993 - Kazuomi]

39
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:53,700
[July 24th, 2000 - Sayaka]

40
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:56,860
- There's Sayaka!
- So adorable.

41
00:04:04,470 --> 00:04:06,100
[When she smiles wide, her eyes close! Cute!]

42
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:08,740
[A big fan of pigtails]
[Feeling like a princess!]

43
00:04:08,740 --> 00:04:10,790
[Class A]

44
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:23,250
Did you add a slide?

45
00:04:27,810 --> 00:04:30,380
This powerpoint isn't the correct one.

46
00:04:32,460 --> 00:04:34,250
Sakuraba?

47
00:04:37,330 --> 00:04:41,610
So, you were Sayaka's classmate.

48
00:04:57,900 --> 00:05:01,420
Did you drug Sayaka

49
00:05:02,340 --> 00:05:04,480
with the sleeping pill?

50
00:05:07,380 --> 00:05:09,290
Sleeping pill?

51
00:05:09,290 --> 00:05:10,920
He lost me.

52
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:13,980
What are you talking about?

53
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,840
This is a photograph from our last ceremony.

54
00:05:19,550 --> 00:05:25,700
As you can see, Sayaka's champagne
has turned a dark blue.

55
00:05:26,780 --> 00:05:27,890
What?

56
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:32,170
Her drink looked normal
in a picture five minutes prior.

57
00:05:32,170 --> 00:05:34,420
Who is he, Sherlock Holmes?

58
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:37,050
Let him have his fun.

59
00:05:37,870 --> 00:05:42,930
As a person working backstage,
your presence would be easily forgotten.

60
00:05:42,930 --> 00:05:46,300
You took advantage of this fact,

61
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:49,230
and snuck up on Sayaka in that time.

62
00:05:49,230 --> 00:05:53,390
You had to have, for one reason.

63
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:59,690
"Your violin performance will begin shortly."

64
00:05:59,690 --> 00:06:03,770
"Please head backstage to get ready."

65
00:06:03,770 --> 00:06:08,760
That'd distract Sayaka from her glass, no?

66
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:25,500
Then you'd simply call for the guests
to drink their champagne.

67
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:28,800
Why would I do something like that?

68
00:06:35,370 --> 00:06:40,680
A student in Sayaka's middle school album
caught our eye.

69
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:46,810
One with your first name, and face.

70
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:50,290
"Honoka Aizawa".

71
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:53,230
That's you, isn't it?

72
00:06:54,260 --> 00:06:57,380
I'll assume your last name
changed upon marriage.

73
00:07:00,070 --> 00:07:02,150
Why didn't you tell us?

74
00:07:04,610 --> 00:07:07,810
So what if we were middle school classmates?

75
00:07:07,810 --> 00:07:09,160
These are baseless accusations.

76
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:12,740
We have proof, of course.

77
00:07:13,550 --> 00:07:14,620
What?

78
00:07:14,620 --> 00:07:18,530
Here's a video from the last ceremony

79
00:07:18,530 --> 00:07:22,900
that captures what occurred,
right after Sayaka collapsed.

80
00:07:26,020 --> 00:07:27,670
One particular individual

81
00:07:27,670 --> 00:07:33,160
had kept her camera rolling the entire time.

82
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:44,780
This is the video from the ceremony.

83
00:07:51,730 --> 00:07:55,370
I wouldn't include it in the slideshow.

84
00:07:57,660 --> 00:07:58,780
<i>Sayaka!</i>

85
00:07:58,780 --> 00:08:00,240
<i>Sayaka!</i>

86
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,510
<i>Sayaka?</i>

87
00:08:10,390 --> 00:08:15,480
You're holding a champagne glass here, no?

88
00:08:16,980 --> 00:08:21,380
You had to retrieve the tainted glass.

89
00:08:21,380 --> 00:08:25,100
After the ceremony, it was reported missing.

90
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:28,780
I heard no one could find it.

91
00:08:28,780 --> 00:08:34,480
Until the next day,
when it had magically turned up again.

92
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:41,180
I suspect you returned the glass,
after washing the substances out.

93
00:08:41,180 --> 00:08:46,270
As a staff member here,
it would be entirely possible for you.

94
00:08:46,270 --> 00:08:49,040
You drugged Sayaka, didn't you?

95
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:55,580
What an unnecessary video.

96
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:04,580
You're correct.

97
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:08,470
I drugged Sayaka.

98
00:09:11,430 --> 00:09:13,840
What the hell? You could've...

99
00:09:13,840 --> 00:09:15,300
Wait.

100
00:09:16,810 --> 00:09:18,520
Honoka.

101
00:09:19,430 --> 00:09:21,040
Why?

102
00:09:23,750 --> 00:09:25,720
Really?

103
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,420
You're asking that, now?

104
00:09:29,620 --> 00:09:32,070
You messed up my life.

105
00:09:32,070 --> 00:09:36,180
What, so she was crazy in middle school, too?

106
00:09:38,770 --> 00:09:41,410
Didn't you all know someone like her?

107
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:46,390
A girl the bullies wouldn't touch,
despite having no backbone?

108
00:09:46,390 --> 00:09:48,960
Well, that's exactly who Sayaka was.

109
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:52,830
Aizawa is indeed my maiden name.

110
00:09:52,830 --> 00:09:57,400
You're right that I was her classmate, too.

111
00:09:57,400 --> 00:10:02,210
But did you know Sayaka and I
were best friends?

112
00:10:03,140 --> 00:10:04,980
Best friends?

113
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:08,150
Why would you hurt your friend?

114
00:10:08,150 --> 00:10:09,700
"Why"?

115
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,760
Has Sayaka ever told you...

116
00:10:17,020 --> 00:10:20,110
about the time she shoplifted?

117
00:10:20,110 --> 00:10:23,380
Shoplifted? Wow...

118
00:10:23,380 --> 00:10:25,580
Sayaka would never. Right?

119
00:10:25,580 --> 00:10:27,410
She did.

120
00:10:28,150 --> 00:10:30,770
You're falling right for her "weak" act.

121
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:31,840
Lies.

122
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:34,820
Sayaka tried to steal a bra.

123
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:37,560
I was her co-conspirator.

124
00:10:38,760 --> 00:10:41,840
We attempted to shoplift together.

125
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:45,300
And we failed.

126
00:10:45,300 --> 00:10:49,260
The rumors spread through the school
like wildfire.

127
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:50,950
But...

128
00:10:52,840 --> 00:10:58,710
I wasn't scared, because I had Sayaka.

129
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:05,970
I planned that shoplifting scheme
for her sake.

130
00:11:10,690 --> 00:11:12,820
And what did I get in return?

131
00:11:14,580 --> 00:11:18,500
She said I forced her to join me.

132
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,300
Sayaka would never lie.

133
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:24,850
Her lie turned me
into the "bad girl" of the school.

134
00:11:26,650 --> 00:11:30,640
Middle school was hell for me.

135
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,080
I'm sorry.

136
00:11:37,580 --> 00:11:39,130
Sayaka.

137
00:11:40,020 --> 00:11:42,540
Don't apologize to a scumbag like her.

138
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:51,380
Our classmates treated me like trash.

139
00:11:52,230 --> 00:11:58,430
They'd call me a "slut", or an "easy girl".

140
00:12:02,850 --> 00:12:08,420
They'd post videos of me,
crawling around to find my school bag.

141
00:12:08,420 --> 00:12:13,220
Sayaka watched it all happen,
without saying a word.

142
00:12:14,770 --> 00:12:17,380
And here I thought we were best friends.

143
00:12:17,380 --> 00:12:19,120
Hilarious, right?

144
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,740
Sayaka couldn't speak up.

145
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:24,900
When I was forced to bow down,
and apologize to her.

146
00:12:26,340 --> 00:12:31,790
She only looked down on me in silence.

147
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:37,440
How did you even feel?

148
00:12:39,650 --> 00:12:41,610
Why did you have to bow down to her?

149
00:12:41,610 --> 00:12:46,000
The bullies. They pressured me to apologize.

150
00:12:49,690 --> 00:12:54,380
I'm sorry I forced you to shoplift.

151
00:12:58,420 --> 00:12:59,400
I'm sorry.

152
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:06,130
Because I was the "bad girl",
who pressured her friend into theft.

153
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:16,740
But you...

154
00:13:18,070 --> 00:13:21,480
You didn't even remember who I was.

155
00:13:22,190 --> 00:13:27,090
I got over my trauma,
married someone I loved,

156
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:30,950
and found my dream job.

157
00:13:31,830 --> 00:13:35,660
I had finally gotten my life back on track.

158
00:13:36,140 --> 00:13:39,240
Only for you to come stumbling in

159
00:13:40,170 --> 00:13:43,010
as one of my customers.

160
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:46,550
It had been a decade since I saw you,

161
00:13:46,550 --> 00:13:48,780
and I still felt like puking on the spot.

162
00:13:49,900 --> 00:13:54,930
That's why you drugged her?

163
00:13:56,470 --> 00:13:58,530
This is ridiculous.

164
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:06,200
- What?
- You have ruined this sacred moment for us.

165
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:10,140
Shut it, you toxic mother.

166
00:14:10,140 --> 00:14:12,250
You're the root of all this.

167
00:14:12,250 --> 00:14:13,280
The root?

168
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:18,890
This woman couldn't stand to see
her own daughter become a woman.

169
00:14:18,890 --> 00:14:22,530
She wouldn't buy a bra,
or menstrual pads for her.

170
00:14:22,530 --> 00:14:25,080
Let alone give her the money
to buy them herself.

171
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:27,220
- That's how this woman is.
- Quiet.

172
00:14:27,220 --> 00:14:29,810
And since she had no money,

173
00:14:29,810 --> 00:14:33,900
I proposed she shoplifted instead.

174
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:40,760
Your daughter had to wear
her one sports bra to tatters.

175
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:43,260
Enough, this is just uncouth.

176
00:14:43,260 --> 00:14:44,750
"Dirty."

177
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:45,960
"Filthy."

178
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:49,080
"Clean up after yourself."

179
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:52,310
That's what you told your daughter
when she got her first period.

180
00:14:52,310 --> 00:14:55,010
I am Sayaka's mother.

181
00:14:55,010 --> 00:14:57,230
I am allowed to raise her as I wish.

182
00:14:57,230 --> 00:15:00,500
That attitude is exactly
what makes you toxic.

183
00:15:01,050 --> 00:15:04,480
Sayaka was only your doll.

184
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:08,570
You were raising her
to look good as a mother.

185
00:15:08,570 --> 00:15:12,030
No one even invited you today.

186
00:15:12,030 --> 00:15:14,720
I have had enough of this slander!

187
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:23,720
I was suspected
of drugging my beloved daughter.

188
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:28,510
Could you people be more disrespectful?

189
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:31,840
Your accusations were entirely baseless!

190
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:34,950
This woman is the culprit.

191
00:15:34,950 --> 00:15:37,670
Everything was her fault.

192
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:41,160
Don't act like you're so innocent, hag.

193
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:42,140
"Hag"?

194
00:15:42,140 --> 00:15:45,440
Your parenting is at fault.

195
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:51,380
Were you irritated to see Sayaka mature?
To watch her become a woman?

196
00:15:51,380 --> 00:15:54,080
Ironic, given you're a woman yourself.

197
00:15:55,980 --> 00:16:02,180
Aren't parents happy see their kids grow?

198
00:16:08,380 --> 00:16:10,610
It's because she's a woman.

199
00:16:11,610 --> 00:16:12,990
Pardon?

200
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:16,960
It's because Sayaka is a woman.

201
00:16:20,430 --> 00:16:25,180
I always wanted a baby boy.

202
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:34,460
What a rotten bunch.
You and your daughter both.

203
00:16:36,170 --> 00:16:37,980
Let's settle down.

204
00:16:38,690 --> 00:16:40,670
You've had enough, no?

205
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:44,080
Sayaka had a stomach ulcer.

206
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:47,050
Your pill may not even be at fault.

207
00:16:47,050 --> 00:16:51,740
My daughter is all better now.

208
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:55,570
We shall simply pretend this never happened.

209
00:16:56,820 --> 00:17:00,950
Now if you will excuse me.

210
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:04,150
Don't run.

211
00:17:04,150 --> 00:17:07,760
You can't turn a blind eye to this.

212
00:17:12,550 --> 00:17:14,460
Please, just stop.

213
00:17:19,290 --> 00:17:20,980
"Stop"?

214
00:17:24,100 --> 00:17:26,820
It's too late for stopping, Sayaka.

215
00:17:26,820 --> 00:17:29,140
Do you want my forgiveness?

216
00:17:29,140 --> 00:17:31,140
Then apologize to me.

217
00:17:31,740 --> 00:17:38,650
"I'm sorry I forgot.
I'm sorry I stomped my friend into the dirt."

218
00:17:38,650 --> 00:17:42,990
Get on your knees and apologize, now.

219
00:18:08,650 --> 00:18:10,980
Don't bow down to her.

220
00:18:12,150 --> 00:18:15,040
What? Still taking her side?

221
00:18:16,410 --> 00:18:18,960
Let me take this opportunity to inform you.

222
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:35,420
Sayaka's exceptional at coaxing out

223
00:18:36,340 --> 00:18:41,370
the "good-intentions" of those around her.

224
00:18:43,050 --> 00:18:48,560
She's a parasite who feeds off of it.

225
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:49,760
That's a bit...

226
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:53,630
And, Kazuomi Hayashida.

227
00:18:53,630 --> 00:18:57,800
You have just become her new host.

228
00:18:57,800 --> 00:19:00,200
Congratulations.

229
00:19:03,970 --> 00:19:05,560
Kazuomi. Kazuomi!

230
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:07,010
Calm down!

231
00:19:07,010 --> 00:19:08,610
Damn it!

232
00:19:08,610 --> 00:19:10,800
Are you satisfied?

233
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:13,730
Drugging your friend for the sake of revenge.

234
00:19:13,730 --> 00:19:18,600
I never wanted to kill Sayaka.

235
00:19:23,090 --> 00:19:24,300
What's so funny?

236
00:19:24,300 --> 00:19:30,040
You would've gotten away with it,
if you knew about the changing color.

237
00:19:31,660 --> 00:19:33,380
Oh, I knew.

238
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,650
I used that pill on purpose.

239
00:19:36,650 --> 00:19:38,050
What?

240
00:19:40,710 --> 00:19:44,400
Your blue champagne
gave me the brilliant idea.

241
00:19:46,210 --> 00:19:52,310
I would mix this pill
into her precious drink.

242
00:19:54,110 --> 00:19:56,370
I wanted to taint her memories.

243
00:19:57,900 --> 00:20:03,930
I wanted her to flounder
in front of all your guests.

244
00:20:05,950 --> 00:20:08,440
That was all I was aiming for.

245
00:20:10,050 --> 00:20:12,500
That, "was all"?

246
00:20:12,500 --> 00:20:17,360
I never thought
she'd start coughing up blood.

247
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:18,690
Your excuses mean nothing.

248
00:20:18,690 --> 00:20:19,940
Kazuomi, back down.

249
00:20:19,940 --> 00:20:24,000
I'm telling you, I never planned to kill her.

250
00:20:29,170 --> 00:20:34,230
Sayaka. You believe me, right?

251
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:43,840
We were best friends, after all.

252
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:09,980
Just so it's known,

253
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:13,960
I drugged Sayaka for her sake.

254
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:16,840
For her sake?

255
00:21:16,840 --> 00:21:19,190
I had to take extreme measures.

256
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:23,160
Or Sayaka would never know pain in her life.

257
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:25,630
That's none of your concern!

258
00:21:28,210 --> 00:21:30,480
You say it was for her sake.

259
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:37,020
But your act of "good-will",
was nothing more than petty revenge.

260
00:21:44,490 --> 00:21:51,380
Try telling the police you meant well.

261
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:56,340
I'm sure they'll be thoroughly convinced.

262
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:03,210
<i>Finally, it's over.</i>

263
00:22:03,210 --> 00:22:05,720
<i>This time for sure.</i>

264
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:11,500
<i>I've snuffed out everyone
who wishes harm on Sayaka.</i>

265
00:22:12,740 --> 00:22:15,370
<i>I've managed to protect her.</i>

266
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:23,440
